node.title: NT records 412 new cases of COVID-19, including 70 of community transmission
node.alt: Natasha Fyles is wearing a pink shirt and looking serious into the distance.
node.description: The Northern Territory reports 412 new cases of COVID-19 — another daily record, says Health Minister Natasha Fyles.
node.content: ["The Northern Territory has reported 412\u00a0new cases of COVID-19 \u2014 another daily record, says Health Minister Natasha Fyles.", "There are 19 coronavirus patients in Territory hospitals, with two people in the ICU and one person on a ventilator.", "Ms Fyles said 70 cases were community transmission, 80 are linked to known case contacts, 71 are interstate arrivals and 191 cases are under investigation.\u00a0", "\"We have got 1,200 active cases of COVID-19 in the Northern Territory,\"\u00a0Ms Fyles said.\u00a0", "\"It is fair to say that we have COVID in every region of\u00a0the Northern Territory and so people when they leave their home, or they have visitors to their home, they should be prepared that they're at risk from coronavirus.\"", "On Thursday, the NT recorded 256 cases of COVID-19 and on Wednesday the territory tallied 117 cases.\u00a0", "Today is the third consecutive day the NT has recorded its highest daily record of COVID-19 cases.", "Ms Fyles said it was \"concerning\" there had been \"significant escalation\"\u00a0in case numbers.\u00a0", "\"We expected this, we're doing large amounts of testing, we've got community transmission,\"\u00a0she said.\u00a0", "\"We can still manage these numbers that we're seeing.\"", "There were 22 cases reported in Alice Springs and one in Tennant Creek.", "\"It's fair to say that the large majority of cases are in the Darwin region,\" Ms Fyles\u00a0said.\u00a0", "\"There's only 19 cases in territory hospitals and the large majority of those for reasons other than COVID.\"", "Territory-wide, 2,810 COVID-19 tests were processed in the past 24 hours.", "More to come."]
